When you eat something with other people, you'd better not blow your nose. You can just excuse <change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>MW</symbol><correct>yourself </correct></tag></change>and go outside and do it. When we pay at a restaurant, usually VAT is included to the price so you don't have to give <change><selection>tips extra</selection><tag><symbol>WO</symbol><correct>extra tips</correct></tag></change>. We don't have tip culture that much, but if you really want to thank, you can do. There will be no one who <change><selection>don't</selection><tag><symbol>AG</symbol><correct>doesn't</correct></tag></change> like to be paid extra. When we greet each other especially if it <change><selection>was</selection><tag><symbol>VT</symbol><correct>is</correct></tag></change> the first time, we bend <change><selection>out</selection><tag><symbol>WC</symbol><correct>our</correct></tag></change> back a little bit and then shake hands. When we drink we show respect to other people. For example, we pour alcohol <change><selection>to</selection><tag><symbol>PR</symbol><correct>for</correct></tag></change> other people first and we <change><selection>grab</selection><tag><symbol>WC</symbol><correct>hold</correct></tag></change> the bottle with two hands. When we pay at a restaurant, usually VAT is included to the price so you don't have to give extra tips. We don't have tip culture that much, but if you really want to thank, you can do. There will be no one who doesn't like to be paid extra. When we greet each other especially if it is the first time, we bend our back a little bit and then shake hands. When we drink we show respect to other people. For example, we pour alcohol for other people first and we hold the bottle with two hands. pairs.text:
Hi, everyone. My name is JoePH and I am running for the president of school council. Truth be told, many other candidate background humbles me a lot. However, I still believe I can make a great positive difference with your help.

First of all, I persuade the principal to build more facility where our students play can enjoy physical activities. There have been many accidents that our students got hurt due to the poor school environment for the sports.
Furthermore, I will act on the quality of food in the cafeteria. Despite of a lot of complaints from the students, our cafeteria has failed to fulfill the demand of our students. I promise to ensure that the quality of the food can be improved. For the worst case scenario, the operation agent of cafeteria can be changed if our expectation is not met.

Lastly, I have been a reliable and trustworthy friend throughout the school life. I will not deceive and disguise myself for my personal gains and interest. I will do my best to keep my promises and achieve those goals with help of yours.

First, you can make your fingers round. It has two meanings. If your round fingers view right side, it means every things VTisOkay. If your round fingers view opposite side, it means money and tip ( in the hotel or store ) .
Second, Korean think manners are really important. Especially, when you inviteWCinvited to dinner, you have to prepare ARalittle gift for him. These presentPLpresents means the Dthanks for invite WCinviting me. Also, when you chew some food, you have to be queitSPquiet and chew it quietelySPquietly. You must eat the food after the adult eat itWChas eaten . If you want to refusalWCrefuse the meeting, you have to call them before DARafew hoursWOearlier whenWCbefore the meeting starts and apologize to your friends ofD parentsWOfriends .

Of course, that if Super- Mart come to our town, many people feel comfortable because of their high quality system and inside of market. But most of small market sellers like me, they wil can't sell anything. Most of customer will go to the Super- Mart. So we will loose our many customers and money too. And this brings me to the next point. What will happen to our jobs and to our future generation? For every job that Super - Mart provides, our town loses 1.5 jobs. I know that you have interests of your citizens at heart and I would be very happpy to discuss this matter further. Anti. S. Uperstore

pairs.text:
Good day everyone! My name is Nayeon Yun. Id like to thank you for being here today and MWalsofor the nomination.

If you elect me for the student council president, I will make sure our school will be a better place to learn and study. I will persuade our professors not to give us any homework on Fridays. I will also hold meetings in the auditorium where concerned students can raise their issues with the President himself.

I will be a responsible and dedicated theD student council president. I will commit my time toMWthe welfare of every single one of you.

I hope I can count on you for support because with your help I know we can make a difference! Thank you.

Dear Paula,
Congratulations on your new job! I could see that you have gone through considerable thinking WCthoughton your spending habits. Here are some tips for you to consider. First, spend some time looking for nearby restaurants offering quality meals at a reasonable price. Eating cheap food may contribute a lot to your goals, but as you mentioned, this could be very unhealthy and may cost you more money in the long run. However, because you also need shops that are convenient enough, try to balance well betweenD healthiness, convenience and low price. Second, make a record of all your expenditures WCexpenses and start cutting backPRon the most unnecessary ones. Facts and data will help you be more objective. Third, talk to your friends and be honest with PRaboutyour financial situation. I understand that it is not as easy as it seems, but it is better to open up than worsen the problem. If you would like, feel free to write me anytime again. I would be more than happy to hear from you!

Wishing you my best,
Jinsol

When it comes to the first group, 15-19-year- old women, we are somewhat optimistic for them. 69% of this group prefer magazines to blogs and this means they will continue to purchase and use magazines for information they want. On the other hand, the second group, 18-24-year-old men, are expected to decrease in the purchase power. Although 72% of them prefer magazines, the magazines should have information about extensive website content. This means men can move to blogs or other websites to get information instead of magazines and we can lose our future customers. However, we should consider other factors beside current purchase rate. The market for women's magazines is more competitve than men's, but it is expected to grow steadily by 6 million until 2025. On the other hand, the market for men's magazines is less competitive, but its size will diminish since 2010. Therefore we should consider these pros and cons carefully before we decide which area we will expand.

So it would be wise to have <change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>MW</symbol><correct>a</correct></tag></change>middle aged model wearing the watch in the ad. Because people in their 20s and younger<change><selection> are tended </selection><tag><symbol>VT</symbol><correct>tend</correct></tag></change>not to wear watches in general. They are very much exposed to digital technology and smart phone with<change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>MW</symbol><correct>a</correct></tag></change> watch in it. In fact I used to wear watch but now I don't wear watch any more. It is too heavy to wear watch on my wrist and I have to clean the watch whenever I wash my hands or face. As far as I am concerned Century watch should prepare for the digital technology in foreseeable future.

pairs.text: I am going to explain the Korean <change><selection>ettiquette</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>etiquette</correct></tag></change>. When you first meet someone, you bow slightly. When you shake an elder's hand, you shake it with two hands. In Korea, elders are well respected, so when they give you something, you have to take it with <change><selection>two</selection><tag><symbol>WC</symbol><correct>both</correct></tag></change> hands. For <change><selection>buisness</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>business</correct></tag></change>, you should always carry a few <change><selection>buisness</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>business</correct></tag></change> cards around and give it to your <change><selection>opponent</selection><tag><symbol>WC</symbol><correct>clients</correct></tag></change>. Make sure to be formal until the people are comfortable with you and trust you. When drinking, women should only pour men's drinks and never another woman's. If you want a refill, drink everything in your cup. If you don't, don't drink all of it. When you are getting a drink poured from someone, you should <change><selection>hld</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>hold</correct></tag></change> your cup with two hands or with one hand holding the cup and the other hand supporting the wrist. If <change><selection>here</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>there</correct></tag></change> is a 'no tipping' sign in a restaurant, then don't. Koreans find it <change><selection>as</selection><tag><symbol>D</symbol><correct></correct></tag></change> an insult if you do. Finally, if someone offers you a gift, refuse it a couple of times, then accept it.

In Korea, elders are well respected, so when they give you something, you have to take it with two hands. For buisness, you should always carry a few buisness cards around and give it to your opponent. Make sure to be formal until the people are comfortable with you and trust you. When drinking, women should only pour men's drinks and never another woman's. If you want a refill, drink everything in your cup. If you don't, don't drink all of it. When you are getting a drink poured from someone, you should hld your cup with two hands or with one hand holding the cup and the other hand supporting the wrist. pairs.topic: Writing an article about NLP techniques
pairs.text: The client worked, and she had a toddler child. She was often busy, and she got annoyed at her child easily when she interrupted her because of the lot of work she had. She ended up staying up late, which made her snappy at her daughter, and she felt guilty. So she went to see a <change><selection>counseler</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>counselor</correct></tag></change>. After the first time there, she tried to find what caused her negative reactions, and the positive intentions behind it. She found out that she felt invaded. Next, she evaluated the situation through multiple perceptual positions. She tried to imagine how her daughter would have felt. From that, they found that there were actually two negative behaviors. One was her daughter's behavior of interrupting her mother's work, and the other was the client's. The reason of her daughter's interruptions were because she wanted some attention, and she didn't know what to do either. So the client and her daughter made a chart of activities for the whole week. That way, the client got more sleep and felt less invaded of her time.

pairs.topic: Writing an article about a superstore
pairs.text:
Dear Mayor Bleak,
I am writing to you to express my feelings about the new Superstore that is planning on being built in our town. I am very worried that doing that will force small businesses to close down. I'm afraid that will make our town lose the feeling of a community. This is probably the main reason 87% of the people in our town oppose to the Super-Mart being built.
Super-market's competition will surely drive the other smaller stores that try to compete with it out of business. Super-Market will also have a wide variety of goods, which is a total of a couple of local stores, which is another way the market can make the other stores go out of business.
Another thing I would lkeSPlike to mention is the fact that our money from taxes and other things will be used on the market, instead of places like schools, where needs are much more urgent right now. That would mean having to cut down on budgets for the whole town.
Please consider my thoughts.

Yours sincerely,
Katherine Cho

pairs.topic: Writing about a disaster relief effort
pairs.text: Dear Mr. Johnson, I'm writing to update you on our progress of the translation project. I'm sure you will be glad to know that we have completed 80% of the project. Since it is for the translation of our website, its quality is very important. Because of this, we hired two experts to double-check errors. Although we identified some errors, we immediately corrected them. At this stage, we are in <change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>AR</symbol><correct> the </correct></tag></change>process <change><selection>to</selection><tag><symbol>PR</symbol><correct>of</correct></tag></change> <change><selection>proofread</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>proofreading</correct></tag></change> them, and I expect we will be able to finish by the end of next week. In fact, I found some vague words, and I need to listen <change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>PR</symbol><correct> to </correct></tag></change>your views on them. So, I would like to request a video conference meeting with you on August 17th? Please let me know your convenient time, and I will try to make my time available <change><selection>on</selection><tag><symbol>PR</symbol><correct>at </correct></tag></change> that time. I look forward to hearing from you soon, Warm regards, K

pairs.text: <change><selection>FTA</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>FAT</correct></tag></change> stands for Free Trade Agreement. This is an agreement that <change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>MW</symbol><correct>says </correct></tag></change>related countries do not impose common external tariffs to promote free trades between the countries. Korea and Chile signed FTA in 2002, but it took two years to be effective because local farmers in Korea strongly opposed. To be effective, the agreement should be ratified by the National Assembly. As you can see, the lawmakers of Korea were concerned on local farmers. That was the first FTA agreement, and the National Assembly ratified it in 2004. I was curious <change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>MW</symbol><correct>about </correct></tag></change>how the first FTA affected the trades between countries after it was effective. First of all, the trade between two countries increased dramatically, 28.3% although average increase with other countries is 14.8%. Secondly, we could increase a market share in Chile from 3. 0% to 7. 2%. Finally, the experience of the first FTA agreement led to more FTA agreements with other countries, e.g. EU, USA,China, etc. However, there might be some critics saying that only the owners of large companies in Korea could get huge benefits, and local farmers were seriously damaged. But, in my opinion, it is way that we should go.

pairs.original: Although Korea has a lower crime rate than other countries, the crime rate has steadily increased for recent decades. The Recent research shows that violent crimes and property crimes make up around four-fifths of all crimes in Korea. Many petty crimes in Korea are punished with fines, although some people like law makers may lose their privileges, including astatus as a lawmaker. If you are sentenced to jail for a petty crime, you might be in prison for a year or less. Consequently, high-profile murders has been increased in Korea. There is a sentence of death in Korea. For an instance, Yoo Young-cheol, the most notorious serial killer, had killed 26 people, and he was ultimately hanged for his crimes. On the other hand, the crime rate in a relation to corruption has been increased as well. Several influential officials such as the head of National Tax Office, the deputy minister of Ministry of Justice, and even former national president have been found guilty of corruption; I mean briberies from the companies. They might be in prison for 2 years or less. I believe that the length in prison should be extended. I want to live in the society without any crimes.%%

pairs.topic: Hosting a group of foreign buyers
pairs.text: Dear Sirs, Thank you for visiting us. I would like to give some tips which can make your journey enjoyable<change><selection> as follows</selection><tag><symbol>D</symbol><correct></correct></tag></change>. First, Korea has <change><selection></selection><tag><symbol>AR</symbol><correct>a </correct></tag></change>long history. And, Koreans are traditionally conservative. There are more people who believe in Buddhism than Christians, so I recommend that you should be careful and sensitive about religious topics. Appropriate business dress is important. Please wear a suit and tie for formal events. When attending a meal with colleagues, please do not blow your nose. This can be considered rude. Many Korean pubic places and private homes do not allow smoking. It is important to ask permission to smoke before lighting a cigarette. If possible, I strongly recommend that it is better for you not to smoke. In Korea, people respect elderly people. In many occasions such as having a meal or drinking, it is quite common that younger people start eating or drinking little later than elderly people. It is not necessary for you to follow younger people, but you can wait until host gives you a notice. I wish you have an enjoyable trip.%% I look forward to seeing you soon. Warm regards, K

pairs.text: As a working mom with a nine-month old son, I believe that a woman who can strike a balance <change><selection>bewteen</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>between</correct></tag></change> life and work is one of the most successful <change><selection>persons</selection><tag><symbol>PL</symbol><correct>people</correct></tag></change>. <change><selection>Rasing</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>Raising</correct></tag></change> a kid takes much care, attention, time, energy, and lastly but not the least, money. I am not saying that working moms work only for money. They need and want to work for self-realization as well. The problem is that being a mom may work as a disadvantage, at least here in South Korea. That is why most moms choose to sacrifice their family over their career. pairs.text: When I read the instruction above, the image of the new city hall of Seoul immediately struck me. The recent-finished city hall building is characterized by <change><selection>eco-friendly</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>Eco-friendly</correct></tag></change> technologies and its highly aesthetic structure. I agree with the former part, but I totally disagree with the latter one. I used to work there. I always thought that the hideous structure looks like an alien on my way to or from work. The city government tried hard to emphasize the <change><selection>eco-friendliness</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>Eco-friendliness</correct></tag></change> of the building, but to no avail. Most citizens are convinced that the new architecture is such an extravagance, a waste of taxpayers' <change><selection>valualbe</selection><tag><symbol>SP</symbol><correct>valuable</correct></tag></change> money. I like the old city hall building much better. It may look old-fashioned, but I had no trouble working up there for the last three years. The old one is actually beautiful as it is sitting right next to the historic royal palace of a breathtakingly fascinating structure. I miss those days I had a cup of coffee looking down on the beautiful palace in my snug office.
